        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 8:29AM EDT by NWS Indianapolis IN</headline>
        <description>At 828 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking heavy rain showers near
Martinsville, or 18 miles north of Bloomington, moving east at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Localized flooding.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Ponding of water on roadways and water pooling in low-lying
areas.

Locations impacted include...
Martinsville, Morgantown, Eminence, and Mahalasville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
